        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "For the Degree of Bachelor of Science in Chemistry, Environmental Chemistry Concentration"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Specialized Curriculum\nGraduation requires grade point averages of at least 2.0 overall and 2.0 in chemistry, mathematics, and physics courses."
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Students in the Specialized Curriculum in Chemistry must include a course in Biochemistry in the Advanced Chemistry area or the Technical Electives area to be certified by the American Chemical Society as having met its specifications."
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Departmental distinction: Students qualify for graduation with distinction by exhibiting superior performance in both course work and in senior thesis research. To be eligible, a student must have a UIUC coursework major grade point average of 3.25, must take CHEM 499 (normally for two semesters) and submit a senior thesis for evaluation, and must have their undergraduate research advisor submit to the department Head a letter of support attesting to the effort invested by the student. The minimum major GPAs for Distinction, High Distinction, and Highest Distinction are 3.25, 3.5, and 3.75, respectively. Final decisions on awarding Distinction honors will be made by the Head or designee.",
        "course_codes": [
          "CHEM 499"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Graduation Requirements"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Minimum hours required for graduation: 120 hours.",
        "credit_requirement": "120"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "University Requirements"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Minimum of 40 hours of upper-division coursework, generally at the 300- or 400-level. These hours can be drawn from all elements of the degree.  Students should consult their academic advisor for additional guidance in fulfilling this requirement.",
        "level_requirement": "400",
        "credit_requirement": "40"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "The university and residency requirements can be found in the Student Code (§ 3-801) and in the Academic Catalog."
      },
